WEBVTT

1
00:00:18.952 --> 00:00:32.899
Remove the pre-cut tiles from the surrounding paper.

2
00:00:32.899 --> 00:00:43.943
Remove the star shaped piece form the center of the Back Panel. This  cut out will allow you to hang the finished tile on the wall.

3
00:00:43.943 --> 00:00:51.584
Notice the score marks that have been pressed into the paper.

4
00:00:51.584 --> 00:01:57.750
Fold along the score marks and press firmly with you fingers.

5
00:01:57.750 --> 00:03:04.384
Using PVA or School Glue, apply a small amount of glue to the smaller tabs and hold in place for 3 to 5 seconds.

6
00:03:04.384 --> 00:03:55.902
Check  the corners for alignment and wipe away any excess glue with a tissue.

7
00:03:55.935 --> 00:04:18.024
For the final step apply glue to all remaining tabs.

8
00:04:18.024 --> 00:04:40.024
Press the back panel down, starting at the folding point. Work your way around the tile pressing the back panel to the tabs.

9
00:04:40.024 --> 00:05:04.237
Try to align the corners of the back panel to the corners of the main body of the tile.

10
00:05:04.237 --> 00:05:12.478
Carefully remove any excess glue.

